pjk@netcom.com (Philip J. Koenig) writes:

>In article <1995Jan20.111111.37456@miavx1>,
>Phillip McReynolds <pamcreynolds@miavx1.acs.muohio.edu> wrote:

>>Has anyone out there got a Promise 4030VL-2 caching controller working
>>with a Mitsumi ATAPI Quad Speed drive under OS/2 Warp?  I'm trying to
>>set the CDROM drive up as the third drive and would like to maintain
>>the SMS access.  The pti1s506.add driver (1.41) doesn't appear to support
>>ATAPI.  Does anyone know whether Promise is developing a driver which will
>>provide ATAPI support?  What about using this setup under plain DOS and Windows
>>under plain DOS?


>My understanding is that caching controllers are usually INcompatible
>with IDE/ATAPI CD-ROM drives.

    The heart of the problem is that the Promise 4030VL-2 lacks an ATAPI 
interface. What you have are 2 somewhat fast IDE (ATA) interfaces that 
may or may not support some of the PIO modes that "EIDE" or "ATA-2" or 
"FastATA" drives use. it does not include the ATAPI interface. it's 
diffrent hardware. Get used to it. PIO Mode 3 != EIDE. though for hard 
drives, it's just as effective. EIDE interfaces have one ATA-2 intrface 
and one ATAPI interface. The ATAPI interface is also capable of mode 0, 
1, and 2 IDE hard drives. 

   DTC makes a cacheing EIDE interface that does indeed have an ATAPI 
interface. DTC controllers suck rocks, tho.

