AlHaz was wrong here...Using the EIDEPromise2300Plus as a reference, any 
EIDE (which I will use to refer to FAST ATA-2 as well) controller has 2 
IDE channels.  As far as ATAPI goes, that is the CD-ROM/tape drive 
standard.  What it means is that any system w/ an IDE controller will 
allow the ATAPI device to run as an IDE device.  Also, EIDE means that 
the controller not only supports HS PIO (aka Mode 3), but also DMA 
transfers.  Anyhow, the reason I suspect your drive is not working is 
that only hard drives are supported as 3rd and 4th IDE devices on the 4030.

